			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=960'>







<img src="http://www.therunes2.com/nanyea/doll.jpg" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Enchanters&message.id=6188#M6188">1</a> of 14
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 554 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Wolja wrote:<BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Nothing here adds utility for raids. I do not now or have ever wanted to be soley a buff bot and third cousin nuker on raids. I know they can do it from some of the events but they have promised class-balance for nigh on three years now. Some action would assist. You and others have posited some great ideas over the years. When Sony works out there are other thinking chanters, other than Nanyea, action may occur, perhaps.</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>Your right Wolja, the problem is they keep quitting/retiring/selling their accounts...&nbsp; There have always been and will be other chanters that seem to be heard alot, thankfully the high wiz-chantress of nukes finally retired... and I could really use some help and other opinions here to help persuade people what chanters could use and what we really need.&nbsp; Probably the biggest blow to enchanters was when they all just quit and accepted what was handed to them.&nbsp; The only place we ever really took a stand was charm, and I think thats what really hurt us... because it is such a controversial issue and the dev team is split on it.&nbsp; They all recognize that is severely underpowered, but no one wants to be the one to put forward a change that suddenly breaks the game stupidly in favor of enchanters.&nbsp; Without a VERY active community which does not exist for enchanters on any board it is VERY hard to rally the support needed to make changes.&nbsp; According to EQPlayers there are tons and tons of chanters out there, in fact its the number 3 most played class.&nbsp; Further fact finding showed that a very significant portion of enchanters quit between 65 and 70, and that almost 2/3rd of the 70 enchanters havent played in almost 4 months.&nbsp; Thats not healthy for any class... so between the snafu that was DX9 engine upgrade, the charm nerf, and the last few months enchanters are on a severe decline... I've been trying to recruit a high end enchanter for months with no luck and no offense but Cestus just took a very sub-par chanter because they were in desperate need too.&nbsp; Most of the uber guilds I know are like this... but its not just uber guilds, its up and down the entire range.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>50-60 has great content for that level, but not for the level of gear people are used to now, and most choose to just powerlevel past it... theres so much 50-60 content in fact that you could play a year straight and still not play all of it, so much storyline that people just skip over because its not worth their time invested v. newer zones.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Unfortuneatly it does fall to me again to bring the bad news, and if not me, it still wouldn't be our fallen Class Correspondent whos working herself to the bone in real life, its another issue but I really wish she would do the right thing and at least tell the community whats going on with her and her duties... and that really leaves very few other people who are gonna step forward and take that big backlash.&nbsp; You guys are mean, and in a way rightfully so because enchanters have been taking hits for the sins of kunark even today the holy trinity haunts us.&nbsp; At the very least you all know who I am, and even if you don't like me or believe me to be some EQ Antichrist, I at least try to keep you guys informed.&nbsp; I really do care about EQ which has been such a big part of my life for the last 6? or is almost 7 years now and the enchanter class is nearest and dearest to me.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>No one is going to magically step forward and say "Enchanter_01" welcome to the EQ inner circle, you will now direct the future of the enchanter class.&nbsp; The community has to come forward, be vocal and intelligent about what they want, present it through the proper and public channels and be active.&nbsp; Passisivity doesn't accompish anything in real life and neither does it work in this game.&nbsp; One of my favorite sociology professors says that the most effective social movements aren't the violent in your face ones, nor the passifist ones, but the ones that are Fiesty... because they stand out, they don't shock and threaten the people in power, nor does it turn off the rest of the community that is vital for their support.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Anyhow I'm going to continue reading the boards daily (which is where I get most of my feedback), using the feedback button, posting, emails, tells, and the like as well as participating in betas and trying to make sure EQ sticks around for the long haul as does the enchanter class.&nbsp; I dont claim to represent the enchanter class, you guys need to speak up and do that for yourself and the rest of us... but I will be there supporting you.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>p.s. as far as my personal agenda for enchanters</DIV>
<DIV>1) Class Reinvisionment</DIV>
<DIV>2) Expansion</DIV>
<DIV>3) Charm</DIV>
<DIV>4) Raid Viability</DIV>
<DIV>5) Group Viability</DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
