			I had a group in Ilsalin. I got 2 mezz resists on a single add. I died before spell gems refreshed, the group wiped. This is not an isolated incident. If I have to explain to sony what is wrong with that picture, then there really is no hope.<br><br>How hard is it to comprehend? We NEED to be able to RELIABLY lock down at least one add, especially in every day XP content. We should not be terrified of adds, they are our job. I hate adds now, I'm just a slower and terrible DPS, coz adds kill me, and that's just pathetetic, and embarrassing and an incentive to explore other avenues of entertainment than my chanter. <br><br>And the buffs, dont forget the buffs... Even with the 4-6 mana per tick of the new KoS thing, we STILL bring less mana regen to group than bards and Beasts and Necros. Make it 10 and people will care.<br><br>It's my favorite item to preach, but we NEED a lure mezz, a long recast, high resist mod mezz. A lesser version of Stasis, somewhere around -50-100 MR and a 1 min recast. Even if it's only 3 ticks and cost like 800 mana. That cant be abused, but it would help us so much, I simply cant emphasise how much.<br><br>And FIX CHARM. Charm was integral to our play style, the core of many chanters and our only solo ability. Yet things like Turn Undead and Manaburn, only optional AA's not core abilities, get more attention? There are dozens of suggestions, heck, I'd even be happy with the ability to summon a wild pet that was charmable, as long as the OoW charm nerf didnt apply. You can even limit them per zone, I dont care, but I want to Wrangle again, and not just for specific raid events.<br><br>(Actually, having a summon line that had us permanently fixed in their hate list would work. If they werent KoS to others, we could even use them on raids, and there would be no way to grief others, coz only us would be on the hate list.)<br><br>Enchanters are rapidly becomming the most boring class to play, as no group uses you for CC, they all get pullers, so all you do is slow and ghetto nuke and buff, and on raids it's even worse. We are emergency, backup CC now at best and that is just WRONG.<br><br>If you want to get depressed, head over to the EQ2 forums, things there get addressed with comparatively lightning speed. And guess what, Enchanters are still the most borked class in the game, coz sony just doesnt understand them at all.<br><br>Until Sony wakes up and realises that their flagship mmorpg is and always will be, EQ, then they will not spend the money to give the Devs teh resources to fix it. Until then, they will continue making juuuuust enough fixes to seem like they are listening, as such the pace of fixes will always be almost imperceptibly slow.<br><br>Such a shame, it really should be in a better state than it is. So shortsighted...	
