			Playing an enchanter from casual to high end raids, from crap gear till top end, i am more than annoyed towards the idea of always wanting to make things easier. I am not a masochist, but dying has always been part of this game at any level and for any class (not only ours). <br><br>What's embarrassing is when we have people posting here that they have no solution to survive a bad pull. It has already been posted here & there several times, between aas (MoM, stasis, doppleganger, etc.) to spells (blur, runes, hi-i-m-the-root-spell etc), passing by equipment and your groupmates, there are enough back-up at this stage of the game. I had suggested a timed aa illusion which would turn us into a non kos illusion to the environnement, sort of complement from doppleganger aa and yet i am not in high demand for this.<br><br>The very one thing that annoys me beyond sense at this stage is the fact that we cannot benefit from a specific mana regen spell as we are a buffing class (i did not say a buff bot) and we only benefit from a universal mana regen spell. Charm has been partially answered with dictate upgrade (not using it that much though) and anyway CoD still work fine ( as a reminder, some of the proposition for changing charm were involving nerfing the whole line, including CoD etc something which annoys me quite a few). <br><br>Anyway, as pointed out in nanyea's post, it's hard for everyone to speak on the same voice (exept for the mezz /ae mezz crap at least) as we don't have the same playtime/goals in one word satisfactions when playing this game. I would say being class correspondant or assimilated and having to pick-ip some of the propositions in order to lobby for your class is certainly not a easy mission. My wish in the matter has always been the same : not gimping our class.	
