			>
			<DIV>I agrre with Unmei in that we havent rolled over and given up Nan,its just that so many of us have asked for the same thing over the years only to be ignored.We can ask again,make new posts,ask for these things all over again and reply to a very similar post to this in about a year when we are asked why we dont have a concerted voice.We do,it's just that no one listens.The devs are more concerned with popping out new expansions because SOE is riding the money train all the way to the bank by giving us a morsel after taking our plate away.Reinvisionment should have been COMPLETED.Instead we had some reinvisionment done which basically crippled us,and then it was forgotten.The devs accomplished what they planned by screwing us and then saying "well we arent done yet,wait for us to finish".When? How long do we have to wait to be made into a viable class again? When WoW and other upcoming mmorpgs take away a larger chunk of the community?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>We needed these changes before WoW hit the market,were ignored,and SOE paid for it by losing over 250,000 players.More games are on the horizon,and SOE is still bypassing the obvious and popping out expansions to a broken game.The question is not how many chanters need to raise their voices before we are heard Nan,but rather how many accounts need to be canceled before they realize there is a problem.</DIV>
