			<div><span><br><blockquote><hr>Unmei wrote:<br>I<br><br>And then there is an entirely different issue - people like Bravor, who seem to believe that everything is pretty much fine, and that people who are dying to single adds are obviously screwing up since they have so many resources. Unfortunately, most of those resources are on long re-use timers, or require the user to live through the casting time. If we are ever to function as CC anywhere nearly as reliably as a monk or a bard, we need to be able to deal with single adds -guaranteed-, without using any resources that take more than a minute or so to recover. The likes of Rune of Shadows, Mind Over Matter, and Color Shock should be reserved for pulls of more than two. It's the &quot;I don't want the game to be too easy! Please don't improve my class!&quot; faction that, in my opinion, has a difficult time discerning between &quot;hard&quot; and &quot;random&quot; and which sends mixed and confused messages to the dev team.<br><br><p>Message Edited by Unmei on <span class="date_text">01-05-2006</span><span class="time_text">11:33 AM</span><br></p><hr></blockquote>I actually never said everything is fine. On the other hand, considering i started this game in 2001 (to bring back memories no hott, tons of people not used with the /assist off command, no aas at all, gear that would make laugh the most casual player etc etc etc) we had not all the back up we have nowadays. The content we experience matches the tool we benefit from, that was what i wanted to underline here. It needs a litle of practice to have good reflex, that won't necessary save you though.<br><br>Anyway, i got to understand why an enchanter in a 2 mobs pull <b>has to live</b> through some beating from resist on mezz or whatever? What's the point in not accepting that sometimes, you are that unlucky that everything will go bad? Reminds me a recent post of a dev that was illustrating this type of attitude taking exemple of people frustrated by not winning at the casino. Iam far from being masochist, but believe me i had my load of deaths, and a lot of times i know i could have done better.<br><br>For anyone browsing this forum (and no, im not refering to you specifically), a dev should be deeply depressed as you could almost think that the enchanter class can't be played. Personnally through the years i have seen my survival geting better &amp; better, and, while geting a top gear definitely helped me, i can tell you that it is certainly not the only reason to explain it.<br><br>Lots of things can be made to improve our class, i did my share of proposal, thanks, and i have no bitterness if they decide to move over. I m not a dev, i have personnally no idea about the difficulties they can experience when coding the game. I know for a fact that 95% of the time, i can log in on a daily basis and play my character without any unacceptable issue (once again, people who started playing long ago (even more for those who started before me) can perfectly understand what i mean as long as their memory serves).<br><br>I understand that we suffer from bugs and limits differently at any stage of the game, though everyone has to make an effort to 'put his/her feet in other's shoes' as we say here.<br><br></span></div>	
