br></span><hr size="2" width="100%"></div></blockquote><div>The critical point you seem to be missing, is that I'm not talking about when you somehow magically screw up on your CC and don't see the mob or something. I'm talking about when you target, mez, resist, aggro, stun, resist, die. On one mob. Your credibility as a viable source of crowd control just got flushed down the toilet.<br></div><blockquote><div><br><span></span><hr size="2" width="100%"><span>For anyone browsing this forum (and no, im not refering to you specifically), a dev should be deeply depressed as you could almost think that the enchanter class can't be played. Personnally through the years i have seen my survival geting better &amp; better, and, while geting a top gear definitely helped me, i can tell you that it is certainly not the only reason to explain it.<br></span><hr size="2" width="100%"></div></blockquote><div>Actually, it probably -does- explain most of it. There -no- XP CONTENT in the game tuned for your level of gear. Therefore, you think &quot;Gee. I'd have to f-up to die here.&quot; You're right. You -would-. But that's because XPing, for someone at your gear level, is synonymous with slumming. (This is, of course, predicated on your having &quot;top gear&quot; - if you don't, well...)<br></div><blockquote><div><br><span></span><hr size="2" width="100%"><span>Lots of things can be made to improve our class, i did my share of proposal, thanks, and i have no bitterness if they decide to move over. I m not a dev, i have personnally no idea about the difficulties they can experience when coding the game. I know for a fact that 95% of the time, i can log in on a daily basis and play my character without any unacceptable issue (once again, people who started playing long ago (even more for those who started before me) can perfectly understand what i mean as long as their memory serves).<br></span><hr size="2" width="100%"></div></blockquote><div>Look. Don't even try to play the &quot;I'm oldschool and you're not&quot; game; Unmei's birthday is May 28th, 2000, and he's not even my oldest character. I can tell &quot;walking barefoot to school uphill both ways&quot; stories until we're both blue in the face.  I know how the game used to be. In case someone needs me to remind them, it used to be that I was reliable crowd control on 4+ mobs. On a pull of less than 5, I would have to do something wrong to die. Compare that to now, when I cannot even control a single mob with 100% reliability without resorting to an AA with a 72 minute re-use timer.<br></div></span><span><div><span><br>That is how it used to be. I'm not asking for a return to that, but I feel it's worth pointing out, that compared to our survivability &quot;back in the day&quot; today is a joke. As is our CC ability.</span><br><span></span></div><blockquote><div><span><br></span><hr size="2" width="100%"><span>I understand that we suffer from bugs and limits differently at any stage of the game, though everyone has to make an effort to 'put his/her feet in other's shoes' as we say here.</span><br></div><hr></blockquote><br>And I have to say that that seems like it is exactly what you are not doing. Take some of your 7000hps worth of HP gear and your 100pts of avoidance, and see how you do in content where tanks at that gear level tank. Don't underestimate what that gear does for you.<br></span><div></div>	
