		" 
			>
			<div>Since it was brought up...</div><div></div><div>I've been an enchanter since June of 2000. I played without AA, without fancy spells, and I wore raw silk for a large portion of my enchanter's life. I used to be able to lock down six or seven mobs, with no resists. Even if they did resist, we had the tools we needed, namely stun, to get things under control and make us able to single mez the mobs.</div><div></div><div>We're lacking in those tools now. As was brought up, a large problem is that if we get large groups, we're limited in how to momentarily get them under control so we can lock them down. Plus there's the issue of resists. I don't want an irresistible mez necessarily, but there should be a much higher -to MR built into our mezzes. We're supposed to be quick on the trigger, not Slowpoke Rodriguez.</div><div></div><div>I'll write more later. At work and break time's almost up.</div>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
