		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div>ok I'm pretty much a lurker, I've posted a few times but I've been doing alot of thinking about the problems the enchanter community is facing and unfortunately the majority of the problems noammount of class tweaking will fix. most of our problems are not derived from our abilities, rather from the abilities and resists given to the monsters we face and no matter what they do to improve our class they are going to have to tweek the monsters by a comparable amount in order to keep the content challenging for everyone else. there is no easy fix for our class unless you want to do a complete overhaul of the game. atleast thats the conclusion I've come to, does it mean I love my enchanter any less, no it just means that I have come to accept that even though I'm unhappy with the way things are I understand that there is no easy solutions and my not even be a reasonable difficult one either.</div>	
		</td></tr>
